        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: allow trusted host-read html after outbound staging",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes Telegram/file outbound delivery for trusted generated `text/html` reports after the attachment is staged into the OpenClaw outbound media store.\n\nPR #87982 allowed generated HTML reports under the OpenClaw temp root, but the live outbound flow loads the original file, copies it to `~/.openclaw/media/outbound/<uuid>.html`, then the channel adapter loads that staged copy again. The second load no longer lives under the temp root, so host-read rejected it.\n\nThis keeps the existing safety checks and adds the outbound media staging directory as an accepted trusted root for generated HTML reports.\n\nFixes #90557.\n\n## Details\n\n- Accept `path.join(getMediaDir(), \"outbound\")` in `isTrustedGeneratedHostReadHtmlPath` in addition to `resolvePreferredOpenClawTmpDir()`.\n- Preserve existing guards:\n  - path must be a regular file\n  - not a symlink\n  - `nlink === 1`\n  - final read still validates text shape and HTML document shape\n- Add regression coverage for HTML staged under a state/media/outbound dir that is explicitly outside the tmp root.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/media/web-media.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint src/media/web-media.ts src/media/web-media.test.ts`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: when an agent reply emits `MEDIA:/tmp/openclaw/<file>.html`, OpenClaw's outbound pipeline loads the file once (`/tmp/openclaw/...` is inside the tmp root, so trusted), stages a copy to `~/.openclaw/media/outbound/<file>---<uuid>.html`, and then the Telegram channel adapter calls `loadWebMedia(stagedPath)` a second time. After PR #87982, the second call rejects with `OutboundDeliveryError: hostReadCapability permits only validated plain-text documents and trusted generated HTML reports for local reads` because the staged path is no longer under `/tmp/openclaw/`. The Telegram message is silently dropped. After this patch, the staged path is also accepted (with the same regular-file / non-symlink / `nlink === 1` / HTML-document-shape guards) and delivery proceeds.\n\nReal environment tested: live OpenClaw 2026.6.1 (commit `2e08f0f`) on macOS 26.4 (Darwin 25.4.0, arm64), Node v26.0.0, Telegram Bot API channel (polling). The original failure was reproduced 4 times on the unpatched build (issue #90557). For this PR the patched code path was exercised in the local repository test harness, since the CI test environment in this checkout cannot drive a live Telegram bot end-to-end.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/media/web-media.test.ts --reporter=verbose\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/media/outbound-attachment.test.ts src/media/store.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/reply-media-paths.test.ts\nnode scripts/check-src-extension-import-boundary.mjs --json\npnpm exec oxlint src/media/web-media.ts src/media/web-media.test.ts\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\n# Pre-patch reproduction (issue #90557, captured via console.error probe in dist/web-media-...js):\n[HTMLDBG] isTrustedPath inside=true   (original /tmp/openclaw/unread-fetch-report.html)\n[HTMLDBG] gate602 trustedGeneratedHtmlPath=true\n[HTMLDBG] isTrustedHtml OK\n# same outbound flow, second loadWebMedia call after staging:\n[HTMLDBG] isTrustedPath inside=false  (staged ~/.openclaw/media/outbound/...html)\n[HTMLDBG] gate602 trustedGeneratedHtmlPath=false\nERROR channels/telegram: OutboundDeliveryError: hostReadCapability permits only validated plain-text documents and trusted generated HTML reports for local reads\n```\n\n```text\n# Post-patch focused regression suite on the PR head:\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/media/web-media.test.ts --reporter=verbose\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  77 passed (77)   # +4 new staged-outbound cases (positive + 3 negative)\n\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/media/outbound-attachment.test.ts src/media/store.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/reply-media-paths.test.ts\nTest Files  3 passed\nTests       69 passed\n```\n\n```text\n# Import-boundary check (no bundled-plugin violations introduced):\nnode scripts/check-src-extension-import-boundary.mjs --json\n[]\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: with the patched `isTrustedGeneratedHostReadHtmlPath` accepting both the tmp root and the outbound staging root, the second `loadWebMedia` call on the staged path now passes the trusted-HTML check, and host-read continues into the existing text-shape / HTML-document-shape validators (which still reject non-HTML, symlink, and hardlink-into-staging cases — these are covered by the new test cases). The previously dropped Telegram outbound is no longer rejected at this gate.\n\nWhat was not tested: live Telegram Bot API delivery from this checkout, because the CI environment lacks bot credentials. The original silent-drop behavior was verified in production on 2026-06-05 by the bug reporter (4 reproductions captured in #90557 with a `console.error` probe inserted into the installed `dist/web-media-...js`); the proof here demonstrates the trusted-root check now accepts the same staged path that was rejected. The same instrumented probe can be re-run on a build containing this PR to confirm end-to-end delivery if needed.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
        "branch": "fix/trusted-outbound-html-staging",
